Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses treewidth, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the use of pebble games in constraint satisfaction and database theory suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper's focus on semantics and categorical structures of computation suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
